name: N-hexyl formate
Reason: 1,3-dioxolane has a melting point of -109.4°C. The basic unit for our comparison will be ethanol, which has a melting point of -114.1°C (according to the CRC Handbook of Chemistry and Physics, 49th Edition, 1968-1969). The structural modifications we need to consider are the presence of a hexyl group. The hexyl group introduces a significant increase in molecular weight and van der Waals interactions, with an approximate increase of +20°C per group, totaling +120°C.
